body:
There are some champs that are &quot;You&#039;re either an X champion main, or you never touch them.&quot;

Champs like:
{{champion:92}} 
{{champion:23}} 
{{champion:107}} 
{{champion:122}} 
{{champion:86}} 
{{champion:55}} 
{{champion:11}} 
{{champion:157}} 
{{champion:238}} 

When you see them, they are **all** lvl 5-7 mastery, and when you look at their profile they have 300,000+ mastery points on them, and their next most played champ is only like lvl 2 or 3.

This is a genuine question, how come its only ever those champions? When was the last time you saw a 300,000+ {{champion:421}}  or {{champion:30}}  that played no other champion? and when you do see other high mastery champs, theres usually not much of a difference between that champ and the next highly played one.

But for some reason those 9 champs are more often than not the only champ that summoner plays. Why? (obviously there are exceptions, but more often than not it seems to be the case.)

Do those champs just attract that kind of person, or are these champs just the most reliable champions to win with if you only want to play 1 champ?

im interested to know why some champs are: &quot;either your an X champ main, or you never touch them.&quot; and others aren&#039;t, and why its generally those specific champs.

{{sticker:zombie-brand-mindblown}}
